{{TagLine|802.11ac Wave 2 Dual-Radio Unified Pro Access Point}} :{{ProductPage|https://www.zyxel.com/us/en/products_services/802-11ac-Wave-2-Dual-Radio-Unified-Pro-Access-Point-WAC6303D-S/overview}} [https://www.zyxel.com/us/en/products_services/802-11ac-Wave-2-Dual-Radio-Unified-Pro-Access-Point-WAC6303D-S/download Downloads] A "Decalration for models" document submitted to the FCC suggests that the [[ZyXEL WAC6303D-S]] and the [[ZyXEL NWA1123-AC SHD]] are electrically identical. * [[ZyXEL WAC6303D-S]]: 802.11ac Wave 2 Dual-Radio Unified Pro Access Point * [[ZyXEL NWA1123-AC SHD]]: 802.11ac Wave 2 Dual-Radio Nebula Cloud Managed Access Point A "Product Equality Declaration" document declares that the differences between these two devices under FCC ID I88WAC6303D-S and devices covered under the I88NWA5123-ACHD entry are the latter lacks Bluetooth and they use different Wi-Fi antennas. {{FCC ST|05/17/2018|indexme.}}
